Description: professional network monitoring and visualization tool
 L0p4Map combines ARP host discovery, full nmap integration, and a
 real-time interactive network topology graph in a dark PyQt6 GUI.
 Designed for security researchers and network administrators who need
 fast, detailed visibility into their infrastructure. Also usable
 headless via CLI for scripting and automation.
 .
 Features:
  - ARP scan with local IEEE OUI database for MAC vendor lookup
  - Hostname resolution via reverse DNS, NetBIOS and mDNS/Avahi
  - Device fingerprinting: TTL-based OS hint, TCP port probing, raw
    SNMP sysDescr query (no external libs required)
  - Automatic role classification: gateway, router, AP, switch, PC,
    Apple, mobile, Raspberry Pi, VM, unknown
  - Hierarchical vis.js topology graph with subnet bounding boxes,
    typed edges and Force Atlas layout toggle
  - Live topology panel showing subnet, gateway, device counts
  - Full nmap integration: SYN, UDP, OS detection, service version,
    NSE scripts, banner grabbing, CVE lookup via vulners
  - Attack Surface view: exposed ports, CVSS scoring, NVD links,
    CSV export
  - Real-time traffic analyser with per-device stats, protocol
    coloring, filter bar, double-click to port scan, CSV export
  - ICMP traceroute with real-time output
  - Multi-interface support, live auto-refresh, graph PNG/CSV export
